Absolutely! You can define your own serialization logic via the `Serialize` trait. Here’s an example: 

```rust
use serde::{self, Serializer};

#[derive(Debug)]
struct MyType(i32);

impl Serialize for MyType {
    fn serialize<S>(&self, serializer: S) -> Result<S::Ok, S::Error>
    where
        S: Serializer,
    {
        serializer.serialize_str(&format!("my_type:{}", self.0))
    }
}
```
This way you control exactly how your type is serialized to JSON.
